ALNG.OL.summary: Awilco LNG ASA, together with its subsidiaries, owns and operates liquefied natural gas (LNG) vessels in Norway. It owns two 156,000 cbm LNG TFDE membrane vessels. The company was founded in 2011 and is based in Oslo, Norway.

WAWI.OL.summary: Wallenius Wilhelmsen ASA, together with its subsidiaries, provides roll-on roll-off (ro-ro) shipping and vehicle logistics services worldwide. It operates in two segments, Ocean and Landbased segments. The Ocean segment engages in the ocean transport of cars, and ro-ro and project cargo primarily for car manufacturers, as well as manufacturers of agriculture, and other high and heavy equipment. The Landbased segment offers vehicle logistics services, including plant and port based technical, marine terminal, and inland distribution services. The company provides its services principally under the Wallenius Wilhelmsen Ocean, Wallenius Wilhelmsen Solutions, EUKOR, ARC, and Armacup brands. It operates a fleet of 126 vessels servicing 15 trade routes. Wallenius Wilhelmsen ASA was founded in 1861 and is based in Lysaker, Norway.
